01:02:35,165 --> 01:02:36,123
Hey!

505
01:03:42,540 --> 01:03:45,915
- Who are you working for?
- Me.

506
01:03:46,040 --> 01:03:48,290
- Who sent you?
- I'm a student.

507
01:03:48,415 --> 01:03:51,373
- Gimme that.
- I've an assignment for class.

508
01:03:53,082 --> 01:03:54,207
Leave me alone.

509
01:04:08,082 --> 01:04:14,290
- Marcy. What's the matter?
- Let's go for a ride, Max.

510
01:04:14,415 --> 01:04:16,207
I can't. I have work.

511
01:04:18,207 --> 01:04:21,706
We had a deal, Max.
Now, let's get in the car.

512
01:04:21,831 --> 01:04:25,831
- Don't ever touch me!
- Max! Max!

513
01:04:25,956 --> 01:04:27,290
- Help!
- Max.

514
01:04:28,915 --> 01:04:31,998
- Leave me alone!
- Max, come here.

515
01:04:32,123 --> 01:04:36,040
Max. Where're you going, Max?
Stop, Max!

516
01:04:36,165 --> 01:04:38,915
- Max! God damn it!
- Help! Help!

517
01:04:40,540 --> 01:04:41,457
Help!

518
01:04:42,540 --> 01:04:44,332
- Get him!
- I got him.

519
01:04:44,457 --> 01:04:45,790
Come here, Max.

520
01:04:48,332 --> 01:04:49,457
Get outta here.

521
01:05:07,539 --> 01:05:11,415
- Where'd he go?
- He's over there.

522
01:05:24,748 --> 01:05:25,998
Max.

523
01:05:26,123 --> 01:05:28,873
Leave me alone!

524
01:05:28,998 --> 01:05:32,040
- I got him.
- Get off of me!

525
01:05:32,165 --> 01:05:36,040
- Help me! Help!
- Get over here!

526
01:05:38,581 --> 01:05:42,623
- Sit down and shut the hell up.
- Calm down.

527
01:05:42,748 --> 01:05:46,706
Didn't your mother ever tell you
not to play with matches?

528
01:05:46,831 --> 01:05:48,539
The market's going to crash.

529
01:05:48,665 --> 01:05:52,415
I didn't do anything.
I don't play the market.

530
01:05:53,248 --> 01:05:55,623
Be careful where you throw out
your trash.

531
01:05:56,040 --> 01:05:58,248
How could you do that?

532
01:05:58,415 --> 01:06:03,123
You gave faulty information.
You dangled the carrot,

533
01:06:03,207 --> 01:06:05,915
but only gave us
part of the code.

534
01:06:06,082 --> 01:06:08,457
Now give us the rest
to set it right.

535
01:06:08,581 --> 01:06:11,123
You bastards!
How could you be so stupid?

536
01:06:11,248 --> 01:06:14,831
Max, you just don't get it.

537
01:06:14,957 --> 01:06:20,207
I don't give a shit about you,
just what's in your head!

538
01:06:20,332 --> 01:06:25,165
If you won't help us, we'll
comply with the laws of nature.

539
01:06:25,290 --> 01:06:29,790
Survival of the fittest -
and we've got the fucking gun!

540
01:06:30,957 --> 01:06:34,498
- Max! Come here!
- Lenny? Lenny!

541
01:06:34,623 --> 01:06:38,623
- Hey!
- C'mon, get in here. Hurry!

542
01:06:38,748 --> 01:06:40,706
Stay down! Stay down.

543
01:06:41,498 --> 01:06:42,790
We've been looking for you.

544
01:06:42,915 --> 01:06:45,831
- What's going on?
- You have the number?

545
01:06:45,915 --> 01:06:48,040
What's going on? What is it?

546
01:06:49,539 --> 01:06:51,374
What're you doing?
Get off of me!

547
01:06:51,498 --> 01:06:52,915
Where's the number?

548
01:06:53,040 --> 01:06:55,790
It's not on me. It's in my head.

549
01:06:55,915 --> 01:06:59,123
You memorised it?
Did you give it to them?

550
01:06:59,249 --> 01:07:01,414
- Who?
- Those Wall Street bastards.

551
01:07:01,540 --> 01:07:03,873
- What do you care?
- Answer me.

552
01:07:05,998 --> 01:07:08,790
Listen. This is really big.

553
01:07:08,915 --> 01:07:12,165
I don't wanna hurt you.
Did you give it to them?

554
01:07:12,290 --> 01:07:14,831
They've got part of it. Let go!

555
01:07:14,957 --> 01:07:17,374
Damn it!

556
01:07:17,498 --> 01:07:19,456
- They're using it.
- Using what?

557
01:07:19,581 --> 01:07:22,706
Shut up! Impetuous little runt!

558
01:07:22,831 --> 01:07:25,915
- Let go!
- No, don't!

559
01:08:06,816 --> 01:08:08,816
Max.

560
01:08:09,566 --> 01:08:11,566
Max.

561
01:08:12,357 --> 01:08:14,357
Max.

562
01:08:15,316 --> 01:08:16,316
Max.

563
01:08:18,524 --> 01:08:20,025
You're all right.

564
01:08:22,066 --> 01:08:25,941
I'm Rabbi Cohen.
Cohen, like you.

565
01:08:27,691 --> 01:08:31,774
I'm sorry for what Lenny did.
He's been reprimanded.

566
01:08:31,899 --> 01:08:35,858
It's not our way. Are you OK?

567
01:08:35,983 --> 01:08:38,025
Yeah.

568
01:08:40,983 --> 01:08:45,315
Max, you have
to give us the number.

569
01:08:47,275 --> 01:08:49,774
What is it?

570
01:08:53,941 --> 01:08:56,899
The Talmud tells us
it began 2,000 years ago,

571
01:08:57,025 --> 01:08:59,191
when the Romans destroyed
the second temple.

572
01:08:59,315 --> 01:09:01,858
What is this?

573
01:09:01,983 --> 01:09:05,108
Max, you'll understand
if you listen.

574
01:09:05,233 --> 01:09:08,691
The Romans also destroyed
our priesthood, the Cohanim.

575
01:09:08,816 --> 01:09:13,108
And with their deaths, they
destroyed our greatest secret.

576
01:09:13,233 --> 01:09:17,108
In the centre of the temple
was the heart of Jewish life,

577
01:09:17,233 --> 01:09:20,191
the holy of holies.

578
01:09:20,316 --> 01:09:24,649
It was the earthly residence
of our God.

579
01:09:24,774 --> 01:09:28,274
The one God.

580
01:09:28,357 --> 01:09:30,649
It housed the Ark
of the Tabernacle,

581
01:09:30,816 --> 01:09:33,566
which stored the original 10
Commandments

582
01:09:33,691 --> 01:09:37,316
which God gave to Moses.

583
01:09:37,441 --> 01:09:41,774
Only one man was allowed
to enter this holy of holies

584
01:09:41,899 --> 01:09:46,191
on one day, the holiest day
of the year, Yom Kippur.

585
01:09:46,316 --> 01:09:48,066
On the Day of Atonement,

586
01:09:48,191 --> 01:09:50,233
all of lsrael
would descend upon Jerusalem

587
01:09:50,357 --> 01:09:54,357
to watch the High Priest,
the Cohen Godul,

588
01:09:54,482 --> 01:09:57,357
make his trip
to the holy of holies.

589
01:09:57,482 --> 01:10:01,649
If the High Priest was pure,
he would emerge moments later

590
01:10:01,774 --> 01:10:04,858
and we'd have a prosperous year.

591
01:10:04,983 --> 01:10:08,316
It meant we were one year closer
to the Messianic age.

592
01:10:08,441 --> 01:10:14,816
But, if he was impure,
he would die instantly

593
01:10:14,983 --> 01:10:18,941
and it meant we were doomed.

594
01:10:19,066 --> 01:10:22,399
The High Priest
had one ritual to perform there.

595
01:10:22,524 --> 01:10:25,357
He had to intone a single word.

596
01:10:25,482 --> 01:10:27,858
Yeah?

597
01:10:27,983 --> 01:10:32,066
That word was
the true name of God.

598
01:10:34,232 --> 01:10:35,608
So?

599
01:10:35,733 --> 01:10:39,608
The true name,
which only the Cohanim knew,

600
01:10:39,733 --> 01:10:42,774
was 216 letters long.

601
01:10:48,025 --> 01:10:50,858
Are you telling me that...

602
01:10:50,983 --> 01:10:55,733
That the number in my head
is the true name of God.

603
01:10:55,816 --> 01:10:59,190
Yes! It's the key
to the Messianic age.

604
01:10:59,316 --> 01:11:02,150
It will take us closer
to the Garden of Eden.

605
01:11:02,274 --> 01:11:05,108
As the temple burnt,
the Talmud tells us

606
01:11:05,232 --> 01:11:07,733
the High Priest
walked into the flames.

607
01:11:07,858 --> 01:11:10,691
He took the key to the top
of the building,

608
01:11:10,816 --> 01:11:14,900
the heavens opened
and received the key

609
01:11:15,025 --> 01:11:18,066
from the priest's
outstretched hand.

610
01:11:18,191 --> 01:11:21,316
We have been looking
for that key ever since.

611
01:11:21,441 --> 01:11:25,274
And you may have found it.

612
01:11:27,482 --> 01:11:30,316
That's what happened.

613
01:11:33,774 --> 01:11:35,816
I saw God.

614
01:11:35,900 --> 01:11:41,357
No. You are not pure. You cannot
see God unless you are pure.

615
01:11:41,482 --> 01:11:44,858
No... I saw everything.

616
01:11:44,983 --> 01:11:50,191
You saw nothing, only a glimpse.
There's so much more.

617
01:11:50,316 --> 01:11:55,399
We can unlock the door
and show God we're pure again.

618
01:11:55,524 --> 01:11:59,566
You're not pure.
How are you pure? I found it!

619
01:11:59,691 --> 01:12:06,691
Who do you think you are?
You are only a vessel from God.

620
01:12:06,816 --> 01:12:09,524
You're carrying a delivery
meant for us!

621
01:12:09,733 --> 01:12:12,191
It was given to me.

622
01:12:12,316 --> 01:12:16,066
It's inside of me.
It's changing me.

623
01:12:16,149 --> 01:12:21,066
It's killing you! Because you
are not ready to receive it.

624
01:12:25,357 --> 01:12:28,399
It's just a number.

625
01:12:29,316 --> 01:12:33,191
I'm sure you've written down
every 216-digit number.

626
01:12:33,316 --> 01:12:36,399
You've translated all of them.

627
01:12:36,524 --> 01:12:41,149
You've intoned them all.
Haven't you?

628
01:12:41,274 --> 01:12:44,107
What's it gotten you?

629
01:12:44,232 --> 01:12:47,065
The number is nothing.

630
01:12:50,149 --> 01:12:53,065
It's the meaning.

631
01:12:53,191 --> 01:12:58,316
The syntax.
It's what's between the numbers.

632
01:13:00,441 --> 01:13:03,941
You haven't understood it.

633
01:13:04,065 --> 01:13:07,941
It's because it's not for you.

634
01:13:08,733 --> 01:13:12,066
I've got it. I've got it!

635
01:13:12,191 --> 01:13:19,316
I understand it. And I'm gonna
see it. Rabbi, I was chosen.

636
01:13:19,441 --> 01:13:22,941
17:13. Personal note.
Getting faster...

637
01:13:23,066 --> 01:13:27,775
You stare into space like that,
you could go blind.

638
01:13:27,900 --> 01:13:31,024
What can the eyes
do without the brain?

639
01:13:36,858 --> 01:13:39,316
14:50.

640
01:13:42,566 --> 01:13:44,983
15:10.

641
01:13:46,316 --> 01:13:48,733
16:55.

642
01:13:49,107 --> 01:13:51,524
10:35.

643
01:13:51,649 --> 01:13:55,066
Already, I'm beginning to see.

644
01:13:59,691 --> 01:14:01,900
Can I help you?

645
01:14:02,024 --> 01:14:04,024
Sol?

646
01:14:04,149 --> 01:14:06,566
Were you a friend?

647
01:14:06,691 --> 01:14:11,483
- What do you mean?
- He had a second stroke.

648
01:15:33,900 --> 01:15:36,941
No! No!

649
01:15:37,941 --> 01:15:39,941
No!

650
01:15:52,066 --> 01:15:56,149
Three! Five! Nine!

651
01:15:56,274 --> 01:15:59,982
Ten! Eight! Six! Five! Two!

652
01:16:36,316 --> 01:16:38,316
Five.

653
01:16:40,566 --> 01:16:42,566
Eight.

654
01:16:44,107 --> 01:16:46,107
Nine.

655
01:16:49,650 --> 01:16:51,650
Seven.

656
01:16:51,775 --> 01:16:56,525
No, Max. No.

657
01:16:56,941 --> 01:16:58,941
Six.

658
01:16:59,066 --> 01:17:02,107
Stay with me, Max.

659
01:17:05,191 --> 01:17:08,066
Max.

660
01:17:15,525 --> 01:17:17,233
No!

661
01:17:17,358 --> 01:17:21,233
It's all right.

662
01:17:23,274 --> 01:17:25,941
It's all right.

663
01:18:54,816 --> 01:18:59,441
17:22. Personal note.
When I was a little kid,

664
01:18:59,442 --> 01:19:02,250
my mother told me
not to stare into the sun.

665
01:19:05,874 --> 01:19:09,749
So once, when I was six,
I did.

666
01:19:35,791 --> 01:19:38,208
Max, Max. Look.

667
01:19:39,292 --> 01:19:41,708
Pretty, huh?

668
01:19:42,916 --> 01:19:45,958
Can we do it, Max? Can we?

669
01:19:46,666 --> 01:19:51,916
How about 255 times 183?

670
01:19:52,000 --> 01:19:54,874
I got it! What's the answer?

671
01:20:08,749 --> 01:20:11,791
I don't know. What is it?

672
01:20:11,916 --> 01:20:15,624
46,665. See?

673
01:20:21,791 --> 01:20:27,417
How about 748 divided by 238?

674
01:20:28,333 --> 01:20:32,208
I got it. What's the answer?

